body:
While it is a good idea to have a place to store the string values and indices of special tokens for a model, and vocab is definitely the place to put it, I wonder if there's a better approach to creating vocabulary classes per use case. Unlike ELMo's vocab, in which the special use of encoding value is involved (and hence a separate class for it), the vocabulary in BERT seems to follow the regular usage pattern that existing Vocab class is intended for.

This points to a drawback of current Vocab design, in which the slots of attributes/special tokens are hard coded. A more extensible way would be to allow users to register whatever special token fields are needed (except unknown token which has special fallback behavior).

@astonzhang @leezu what do you think?
